# The following are steps to run the RNA-seq analysis from Hertz, et. al. 
# 20 March 2025
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# File Key
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Variant_Genome.fasta
This FASTA file is the full length RNA transcrip of all sequences in the oligo pool

### LMH_1_GitHub.out.sam
This .sam file is the first 10000 lines of the STAR output for sample LMH_1

### Read_Classification_SUBMIT.ipynb
This Jupyter notebook takes **.out.sam** files and compiles the read length to each variant then assess transcription termination.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The following are the commands for generating a genome for STAR from Variant_Genome.fasta
# 10 May 2025
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Assemble DNA sequences into a genomic assembly
module load megahit/1.0.6.1
megahit -o megahit_Variant_genome_directory -r Variant_Genome.fasta

# Generates the necessary genome index files for STAR to efficiently map reads to a reference genome
module load STAR/2.7.9a
STAR --runMode genomeGenerate --genomeDir megahit_Variant_genome_directory --genomeFastaFiles Variant_Genome.fasta --genomeSAindexNbases 8
